    <stitle>Lucas Varity/TRW Hydraulic Antilock Brake System - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0403936">ELECTRONIC CONTROL UNIT</hotlnk>
            </title>
            <figure id="f0403936" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g0403936" filename="../figg04/G0403936.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Electro-Hydraulic Control Unit</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ECU BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ECU TO HCU INTERCONNECT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ECU BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. ELECTRO HYDRAULIC CONTROL UNIT (EHCU)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>In some installations there may not be enough room to remove the ECU from the EHCU without
                        removing the EHCU. If the ECU needs to be replaced, it is advantageous to remove the ECU without
                        removing the EHCU.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Avoid touching the pins of the electrical connectors on the ECU. Damage could occur, due to
                        electrostatic discharge.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the negative battery terminal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk document="s040393_6.xml" xrefid="f0403908">Disconnect the 2-way and 24-way electrical
                        connectors from the ECU
                        <xref refid="f0403908"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It may be necessary to cut retainers and move the wire harness to gain access to the
                        electrical interconnect.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the 2-way connector from the electrical interconnect between the ECU and HCU
                    (it is located on the side of the EHCU next to the frame rail).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk document="s040393_51.xml" xrefid="f0403938">Remove the four Torx&#174; bolts that fasten the
                        ECU to the HCU
                        <xref refid="f0403938"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Always insure surfaces and gaskets are kept clean to prevent contamination.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the ECU from the HCU. A light amount of force may be required.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
